The paper discusses the construction and applications of wavelet trees and wavelet suffix trees, which are data structures commonly used in string algorithms and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses rank/select problems, which are commonly studied in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.DM). The use of wavelet trees in compression algorithms also suggests a possible category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the use of machine words and word RAM model, which are topics commonly studied in theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
